LanguageData.SRABarrierTooltip:
Barriers can block incoming damage.

-Barriers have barrier efficiency. Damage taken is multiplied by barrier efficiency before calculating barrier value loss.
-Barriers calculate the unit's damage taken multiplier and multiply it with barrier efficiency. If the damage taken multiplier is above 100%, it will not be included in the calculation.
-Some barriers have recharge cooldown. If the barrier is completely destroyed, it enters recharge cooldown. When cooldown time is greater than 0, the barrier will fully recharge immediately after cooldown completes.
-Some barriers have damage cap. Damage taken will not exceed this cap. Only effective when this value is greater than 0.
-Some barriers have damage reduction. Damage taken is reduced by the corresponding value. Only effective when this value is greater than 0.

-Regen Delay: {0}
-Recharge Cooldown: {1}
-Barrier Efficiency: {2}
-Damage Cap: {3}
-Damage Reduction: {4}
